<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352388>
    dc:description "Figure 1-4. Propygidia of Nearctic Ochodaeinae genera. Scale bars = 0.5 mm. 1) Unmodified propygidium of Cucochodaeus sparsus, with elytral apices evenly rounded. 2) Two tubercles present on apex of propygidium in Parochodaeus duplex, dentate elytral apices also shown. 3) Elongate propygidium with subparallel sulcus in Xenochodaeus simplex. 4) Short propygidium with trapezoidal sulcus in Neochodaeus praesidii, arrow indicates stridulatory peg." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5352388/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

